folder: Central Park West & 72nd Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Central Park: The Lake, a view west towards 72nd Street, which is shown in the background in line with the bridge.
The old Majestic Hotel is shown on the S.W. corner of Central Park West and 72nd Street, and the Dakota apartment house, one of the oldest in New York, on the N.W. corner. The building in the block from 73rd to 74th Streets is the Langham.
1923.

P. L. Sperr.

folder: Central Park West & 72nd Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
(1)
The Dakota, one of the oldest apartment houses in New York, Central Park West, west side, from 72nd to 73rd Streets, from south-bound drive, Central Park at about 70th Street. At the left may be seen a portion of the Majestic Hotel, now replaced by the Majestic Apartment House.
October 13, 1927.
P. L. Sperr, Photographer.
(2)
A closer view of the Dakota.
February 2, 1929.
P. L. Sperr, Photographer.
